<p align="center" style="font-size: 22px;"><strong>Getting Started on   Synergychat</strong> <br />
  <br />
  <br />
</p>
<p class="red"><strong><U>Step 1 Setup up   Groups and Define appearance to guests.</U></strong> <br />
</p>
<p>1.Go to the CONTACTS AND GROUP   tab</p>
<p>2.Click on GROUPS</p>
<p>3.Click ADD GROUP <br />
</p>
<p><img src="../img/cg.jpg" width="320" height="148" />  <br />
</p>
<p  class="red"><strong><U>STEP 2 Enter Group or   Member Name</U></strong></p>
<p>Enter the name of the Group or Individual   you want to treat as a group in the fields below and set an email to forward   offline messages when you do not answer chat. </p>
<p><img src="../img/group1.JPG"/>  <br />
</p>
<p><strong>There are 3 settings for privacy   below: </strong></p>
<p><strong>1) Public</strong> - Guests can view the   group name but not any individuals associated with this group. Any guest who   clicks on the group name will be directed to a guest wait list         for   operators attached to this group. Offline messages are generated if no answer to   an email designated to that group in Synergy. <br />
</p>
<p><strong>2) Private </strong>- The group name and   individuals associated with the group are completely hidden from all guests. The   group will only show for the registered members of Synergy for your   account. <br />
</p>
<p><strong>3) Individual </strong>- Guests will see   the group name as well as all individuals associated with the group. The   individual names are listed beneath the group name so that guests can contact   anyone listed that is online. <br />
  <br />
  <br />
</p>
<p  class="red"><strong><U>Step 2 Add   Users</U></strong> <br />
</p>
<p>After you have created your groups you   can add individual users to each group. Enter user information, assign the user   to any of the groups selected and set the password for the user. <br />
</p>
<p><img src="../img/cuser.jpg"/></p>
<p  class="red"><strong><U>Step 3 Appearance and   Installation  (Installing the Cloud)</U></strong> <br />
</p>
<p>Chose your button to appear on your site   and click generate code. If you want to use your own graphic please replace   /LiveChatButton1.jpg&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with a graphic of your own. Install code in   the body of the HTML page where you wish to place the button.   <br />
</p>
<p><img  src="appp.jpg" />  <br />
  <br />
</p>
<p align="center"><strong><U>AFTER   INSTALLATION</U></strong> <br />
  <br />
  <br />
</p>
<p  class="red"><strong><U>CHAT   LOGS</U></strong></p>
<p>Allows you to monitor all members   individual text conversations. These are accessible only within the main   SynergyChat administrative account login and not individual user   login. <br />
  <br />
</p>
<p class="red"><strong><U>EMAIL   LOGS</U></strong></p>
<p>Stores all emails submitted by guests for   future contact purposes. <br />
</p>
<p><img src="../img/logs.jpg" />  <br />
<img src='mail icon.jpg'"/></p>
<p class="red"><strong><U>VIDEO   EMAIL</U></strong></p>
<p>Allows you to record a message through   your browser and email the video message to anyone. The video message is stored   on the Cloud and not on your computer. The recipient of the video email will be   provided with a link to a secure page in order to watch the video on their   browser.  <br />
</p>
<p><strong>STEP 1- </strong>Record the video by   clicking the record button. When finished recording stop.</p>
<p><strong>STEP 2- </strong>Review the video by   pressing play. If you wish to delete the video and re-record simply press record   again. You will be asked if you wish to re-record in which the video will be   erased and a new video will be created.</p>
<p><strong>STEP 3- </strong>Once satisfied with the   video simply add the title and click save. </p>
<p><strong>STEP 4- </strong>Send the video message by   entering the email address or multiple addresses in the email field. You may   also click on other registered members listed on the left which will   automatically enter their email in the email field. <br />
</p>
<p><strong>STEP 5-</strong> Click send to notify each   recipient of the video message. Each recipient will receive a link in the email   to view the video message on their browser. <br />
</p>
<p><strong>VIEW VIDEOS</strong>- This provides a list   of saved video messages to review, send or delete. All video messages will be   saved on the cloud and will only be removed by the user who recorded the   message. </p>
<p> </p>
<p> <img  /><br />
</p>
<p><img src="../img/i.jpg"  /></p>
<p class="red"><strong><U>FACE TO FACE VIDEO   CHAT  </U></strong></p>
<p>Face to face video chat is conducted   either between Synergy members or a member as well as a guest.  <br />
</p>
<p><strong>GUEST TO MEMBER</strong>- Guests click on   the button installed on the website. The guest then chooses to chat with an   individual or group listed by simply clicking on the name. When a guest clicks   on a group or individual they are prompted to enter their name and email   address. Once the guest has entered their information a text-only chat dialog   will appear. The operator must then click “start video chat” in order to conduct   a face to face video chat. The operator may also chat without video if desired   by not clicking the “start video chat”. Guests are not allowed to initiate video   chat unless the operator wishes to. Please note: A guest does not need a camera   in order to conduct a video chat, they can still see the operator.</p>
<p><img src="../img/guest123.JPG"  /></p>
<p><img src="../img/guest45.JPG"  /></p>
<p><img src="../img/guest6.JPG"  /><br />
<strong>MEMBER TO MEMBER</strong>- When a member is   logged into their account, simply click a name on the name list. The other   member will be notified of a request to video chat or just text.</p>
<p><img src="../img/member2.JPG"  /><br />
Member1                                                              Member 2<br />
<img src="../img/member3.JPG"  /></p>	
<p><img src="../img/member4.JPG"  /> <br />
  <br />
  
</p>
<p><strong><U>VIDEO CONFERENCE UP   TO 9 PEOPLE</U></strong></p>
<p>A live face to face video conference can   be conducted with up to nine people simultaneously. <br />
</p>
<p>STEP 1- Click on the video conference   icon on the left. <img src="../img/vconf icon.jpg"  /></p>
<p><img src="../img/conf1.JPG"  /></p>
<p>STEP 2- Enter the emails of the   individuals you wish to invite to the video conference or simply click on the   left to add Synergy members. Up to 8 guests may attend requiring  only one   Synergy member.</p>
<p><img src="../img/conf2.JPG" alt=""  /></p>
<p>STEP 3- Enter date, time and subject of   the video conference. </p>
<p>STEP 4- Click “create conference”.    <br />
<p><img src="../img/conf3.JPG" alt=""  /></p>
</p>
<p>ACCESS VIDEO CONFERENCE- Each attendee,   as well as the member who created the conference, will receive an email   containing a link to the video conference. The conference date, time and subject   will be provided in the email. Once the attendee clicks </p>
<p>on the link they will be directed to a   secure "video conference" page. </p>
<p>.</p>
